OL,3,CWales' disability employment gap is
OL,4,Cthe worst in Britain
OL,6,FWales' disability employment gap is
OL,7,Fconsistently higher than anywhere else
OL,8,Fin Britain, according to a recent
OL,9,FSenedd report.
OL,11,FThe disability employment gap refers
OL,12,Fto the difference in employment rates
OL,13,Fbetween disabled and non-disabled
OL,14,Fpeople.
OL,16,FResearch shows only 4.8% of people
OL,17,Fwith learning disabilities are in
OL,18,Fwork, and there are considerable
OL,19,Fvariations between local authority
OL,20,Fareas.
